<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 03-12-05 - Injector And Glow Plug Harness Change</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi031205" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>03-12-05</tsinumber>
        <replace>
            <tsinumber>02-12-07</tsinumber>
        </replace>
        <tsidate>April, 2003</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engine</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Injector And Glow Plug Harness Change</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>T 444E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI replaces TSI 02-12-07 to modify the harness tool number.</para>
                <figure id="p014901" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/F0809.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             scalefitheight="272px" box="yes"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. 5-Pin Connector and 9-Pin Connector</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>5-Pin Connector</callout1>
                        <callout1>9-Pin Connector</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>Starting with engine serial number 7.4HM2U0661894 (engine build date 12/11/1997), the injector and
                    glow plug wiring harness was changed from two 5-pin connectors to one 9-pin connector at each valve
                    cover. This change included engine wiring harness, valve cover gasket and UVC (Under Valve Cover)
                    harness.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <para>The ZTSE4458 breakout tee enables the testing of the glow plug and injector circuits without the
                removal of the valve covers. This tool was a "direct ship" to Dealers.
            </para>
            <figure id="p014903" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/F0808.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. ZTSE4458 Glow Plug And Injector Breakout Tee</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The following information assists in the diagnostics of the glow plug and injector circuits utilizing
                the new 9-pin connector.
            </para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Some engine wiring harnesses had the glow plug wires switched on the valve cover connector
                        (97GP1 and 97GP3 or 97GP2 and 97GP4). This does not affect the glow plug operation. However, if
                        wire numbers are checked at the connector, they may not match the numbers on the wiring diagram
                        and diagnostic literature. It is recommended to leave the wires in the current locations.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="p014904" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/F3301.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. T 444E Glow Plug Control (GPC) 9-Pin Connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="tp014901" tblwidth="col-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>GLOW PLUG RELAY OPERATION (VOLTAGE CHECKS AT RELAY)</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="122.00px"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="63.00px"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="313.00px"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>
                                    <title>Test Points</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>
                                    <title>Spec.</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>
                                    <title>Comments</title>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>B+ terminal to Ground</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>B+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Relay switch power, B+ should be present at all times (terminal with single
                                    6-gauge wire). Check connection at starter or fusible links if no power (voltage)
                                    present.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Glow Plug Feed (97GPX &#38; 97GP) to Ground</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>B+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Glow plug feed voltage should be present 10 to 120 sec. after key is cycled On,
                                    dependent upon battery voltage, barometric pressure (altitude) and engine coolant
                                    temperature. (Large terminal with 2 wires.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Circuit 97CH to Ground</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>12V, or 0V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Glow Plug Control ECM commands relay On = 12V Off = 0V</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Circuit 97GR to Ground</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>0V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>GPC relay grounded thru ECM - If voltage present, check circuit for open.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
